==English==

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Of or pertaining to the direction of one liquid or other mass travelling into another: [[incoming]], [[inflow]]ing.
#:''The effluent sewage comes in from the north; the treated affluent is dumped into the river on the south''. 
#:''The effluent paperwork is handled by Intake; we then process it and send it on.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A body of water tributary to another.
#:''The Ohio River is an effluent of the Mississippi River.''
#:: Compare: ''The Mississippi is an [[affluent]] of the Ohio.''
#Sewage water that has been (partially) treated, and is released into a natural body of water.

